<inglise> Whereas Article 5 of Council Regulation No 136/66/EEC of 22 September 1966 on the establishment of a common organization of the market in oils and fats (4), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2260/84 (5), introduced a system of production aid for olive oil; whereas this aid in respect of areas under olives at a certain date is granted to growers who are members of the producer organizations specified in Article 20c (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 136/66/EEC and whose average production is at least 100 kilograms of oil per marketing year and to other growers on the basis of the number and production potential of olive trees and of the yields of such trees, as determined according to a standard method, and provided that the olives produced have actually been harvested; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu 22. septembri 1966. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 136/66/EM&Uuml;, &otilde;li- ja rasvaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kehtestamise kohta, (4) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2260/84, (5) artiklis 5 on kehtestatud oliivi&otilde;li tootmistoetuste s&uuml;steem; k&otilde;nealune toetus teataval kuup&auml;eval oliivikasvatuseks kasutatavate alade jaoks antakse kasvatajatele, kes on m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 136/66/EM&Uuml; artikli 20c l&otilde;ikes 1 kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud tootjaorganisatsiooni liikmed ja kelle keskmine toodang on v&auml;hemalt 100 kg &otilde;li turustusaastas, ning teistele kasvatajatele oliivipuude arvu ja tootmispotentsiaali ning nende puude &uuml;htse meetodiga m&auml;&auml;ratud saagise p&otilde;hjal, tingimusel et kasvatatud oliivid on tegelikult koristatud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas experience has shown that, despite the existence of rules providing for numerous specific controls, there are problems as regards ensuring timely and effective control; whereas this could lead to an unwarranted financial burden on the Community; </inglise>
