<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Without prejudice to Article 2, if a check at a mill shows irregularities including a substantial difference between the quantities of olives pressed or oil produced and the quantities shown in the stock records, or inadequacy in the stock records, or in communication thereof, the Member State concerned shall withdraw approval from the mill in question for a period of between one and five marketing years. </inglise>
<eesti> Ilma et see piiraks artikli 2 kohaldamist, kui pressimisettev&otilde;tte kontrollimisel ilmnevad rikkumised, millega kaasneb oluline erinevus pressitud oliivide v&otilde;i toodetud &otilde;li koguste ja laoarvestuses osutatud koguste vahel, laoarvestuse ebat&auml;ielikkus v&otilde;i rikkumine sellest teavitamisel, t&uuml;histab asjaomane liikmesriik k&otilde;nealuse pressimisettev&otilde;tte tunnustuse &uuml;heks kuni viieks turustusaastaks. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> For the purpose of determining the period for which recognition or approval is to be withdrawn, the competent authority shall take into account both the gravity and the duration of the infringement. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rates ajavahemikku, milleks tunnustus v&otilde;i kinnitus t&uuml;histatakse, peab p&auml;dev asutus v&otilde;tma arvesse nii rikkumise raskust kui ka kestust. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
<inglise> Throughout the period covered by the withdrawal of recognition or approval referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2, no new recognition or approval may be granted by the Member State concerned following an application intended to circumvent the sanction imposed. </inglise>
<eesti> Kogu l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 osutatud tunnustuse v&otilde;i kinnituse t&uuml;histamise ajal ei v&otilde;i asjaomane liikmesriik anda uut tunnustust ega kinnitust taotluse alusel, mille eesm&auml;rgiks on kehtestatud sanktsioonidest k&otilde;rvalehoidmine. </eesti>
<inglise> Should the withdrawal of a mill's approval have serious consequences for the pressing facilities in a given production zone, it may be decided to allow the mill to operate under special arrangements. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui pressimisettev&otilde;tte kinnituse t&uuml;histamisel on t&otilde;siseid tagaj&auml;rgi pressimist&ouml;&ouml;stusele asjaomases tootmispiirkonnas, v&otilde;ib lubada pressimisettev&otilde;ttel t&ouml;&ouml;tada erikorra alusel. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> Detailed rules for the application of this Regulation shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 38 of Regulation No 136/66/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaldamise &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad v&otilde;etakse vastu m&auml;&auml;ruse nr 136/66/EM&Uuml; artiklis 38 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall communicate to the Commission the measures they have taken pursuant to this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel v&otilde;etud meetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub selle avaldamise p&auml;eval Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 November 1984. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rus kehtib alates 1. novembrist 1984. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
